  "description": "A comprehensive database export compiled for the IS477 project. This dataset integrates object metadata and collection information, combining records from [the Objects Dataset: https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/PranathiSagi/IS477-Sagi-Kidwell-Shafer/refs/heads/main/museum_db_export/objects.csv], [the Media Dataset: https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/PranathiSagi/IS477-Sagi-Kidwell-Shafer/refs/heads/main/museum_db_export/media.csv], [the Media Relationships Dataset: https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/PranathiSagi/IS477-Sagi-Kidwell-Shafer/refs/heads/main/museum_db_export/media_relationships.csv], [the Constituents Dataset: https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/PranathiSagi/IS477-Sagi-Kidwell-Shafer/refs/heads/main/museum_db_export/cons.csv], [the Objects Constituents Dataset: https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/PranathiSagi/IS477-Sagi-Kidwell-Shafer/refs/heads/main/museum_db_export/objects_cons.csv], and [the Text Entries Dataset: https://media.githubusercontent.com/media/PranathiSagi/IS477-Sagi-Kidwell-Shafer/refs/heads/main/museum_db_export/text_entries.csv]. It provides a unified structure for analyzing museum artifacts, including provenance and acquisition history. All these datasets help us compare the traditional and digital artworks at the National Gallery of Art Museum dataset to answer our research questions when determining the relationship between these two artworks. This helps us see whether digital or traditional media artworks are more represented in the National Gallery of Art Museum to help us understand which works of art of being included versus excluded.",
